---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/main.astro';
---

<MainLayout content={{ title: 'Scientific Publications | AI Secure Software Development' }}>
  <section class="container mx-auto py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Scientific Publications</h1>
    
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Year Section -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">2023</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Publication Item -->
          <div class="bg-card p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">AI-Powered Static Analysis for Vulnerability Detection: A Comparative Study</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">Smith, J., Doe, J., Chen, E.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              This paper presents a comparative study of various AI-powered static analysis techniques for detecting 
              vulnerabilities in source code. We evaluate the effectiveness of different machine learning models and 
              feature extraction methods on a diverse dataset of vulnerable code samples.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                PDF
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                Code
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                DOI
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Publication Item -->
          <div class="bg-card p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Secure by Design: Integrating AI into the Software Development Lifecycle</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">Chen, E., Smith, J., Johnson, R.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              This paper proposes a framework for integrating AI-powered security tools into the software development 
              lifecycle. We demonstrate how AI can be used at different stages of development to identify and mitigate 
              security vulnerabilities before they reach production.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                PDF
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                DOI
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Year Section -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">2022</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Publication Item -->
          <div class="bg-card p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Learning to Generate Secure Code: A Transformer-Based Approach</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">Doe, J., Smith, J., Lee, M.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              This paper presents a novel approach to generating secure code using transformer-based models. 
              We train our model on a large corpus of secure code examples and demonstrate its ability to 
              generate code that adheres to security best practices.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                PDF
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                Code
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                DOI
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Publication Item -->
          <div class="bg-card p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Automated Vulnerability Repair using Deep Learning</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">Chen, E., Doe, J., Wilson, T.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">
              This paper explores the use of deep learning techniques for automatically repairing security 
              vulnerabilities in source code. We develop a model that can identify vulnerabilities and 
              suggest appropriate fixes, reducing the time and effort required for security remediation.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                PDF
              </a>
              <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 bg-primary/10 text-primary rounded-full text-sm">
                DOI
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout> 